            "answer_text": "They aren\u2019t. Marketers are. They have have something to differentiate themselves. And then everyone suddenly has to do the same thing. I would prefer thicker bezels. Those bezels keep your fingers off the screen which means you don\u2019t always end up launching apps by accident, and a drop is far less likely to break the screen. But marketers don\u2019t care about that. They just want the phone to be pretty. But pretty soon they all look alike. ",
